program.lineStr: 0                                   :ASSERT ; Ensure it is the beginning of the execution

E                                   :MSTORE(lastTxHashId) ; Points at first hash address to be used when processing transactions

$ => A          :MLOAD(ctxTxToUse) ; Load first context used by transaction
0 => A, D, E, CTX, PC, MAXMEM, SR, HASHPOS, RR        :JMP(start)
HASHPOS                         :MSTORE(sigDataSize) ; save bytes length added to ethereum transaction hash
A => E          ; Store sumResult on E
${_addMod / A} => B        ; k: Max should be (2^256 -1) * 2 / 2 --> smaller than 2^256
$              :MLOAD(arithRes1), ARITH ; Can this be on the same line of MLOAD?
$ => B          :MLOAD(SP--) ; sign byte --> sign bit = 8 * A + 7
$               :LT, JMPC(opSIGNEXTENDEnd); if signByte is 31 or more, means basically let the number as it is
B * 8  + 7 => B ; B is less than 31, no need for binary
${exp(2, B)} => A  ; signBit TODO table for shifting + multipliyng
$               :EQ, JMPC(opSIGNEXTENDPositive) ; If 0 means the sign bit was 0 --> positive
0 => HASHPOS ; A new hash with position 0 is started
${A + B} => B                   ; TODO: This is UNSAFE
0 => C                                                            ; 3rd parameter does not apply to nonce or balance
$ => A              :MLOAD(lastCtxUsed)                           ; Set the CTX and store in system
$ => A          :MLOAD(lastCtxUsed)                           ; Set the CTX and store in system
$ => A          :MLOAD(lastCtxUsed)                           ; Set the CTX and store in system
$ => A          :MLOAD(lastCtxUsed)                           ; Set the CTX and store in system
0 => C                                                            ; 3rd parameter does not apply to nonce or balance
$ => A              :MLOAD(lastCtxUsed)                           ; Set the CTX and store in system
$ => A          :MLOAD(lastCtxUsed)                           ; Set the CTX and store in system
$ => A          :MLOAD(arithRes1); in: [arithA, arithB] out: [arithRes1: arithA/arithB, arithRes2: arithA%arithB]
GAS - A => GAS  :JMPN(outOfGas)  ; dynamic_gas = 6 * minimum_word_size + memory_expansion_cost
:CALL(MLOAD32); in: [E: offset] out: [A: value, E: new offset]
:CALL(MLOADX); in: [E: offset, C: length] out: [A: value, E: new offset]
:CALL(SHRarith); in: [A: value, D: #bytes to right shift] out: [A: shifted result]
:CALL(divARITH); in: [arithA, arithB] out: [arithRes1: arithA/arithB, arithRes2: arithA%arithB]
:CALL(MLOADX); in: [E: offset, C: length] out: [A: value, E: new offset]
:CALL(SHRarith); in: [A: value, D: #bytes to right shift] out: [A: shifted result]
B + 1               :MSTORE(nextFreeLogIndex) ; store next free log index
:CALL(MLOADX); in: [E: offset, C: length] out: [A: value, E: new offset]
:CALL(readPush); in: [D: bytes to read] out: [E: value read]
:CALL(SHLarith); in: [A: value, D: #bytes to left shift] out: [A: shifted result]
:CALL(MLOADX); in: [E: offset, C: length] out: [A: value, E: new offset]
:CALL(SHRarith); in: [A: value, D: #bytes to right shift] out: [A: shifted result]
:CALL(MLOAD32); in: [E: offset] out: [A: value, E: new offset]
:CALL(offsetUtil); in: [A: offset] out: [E: offset/32, C: offset%32]
B               :MEM_ALIGN_WR8 ; only use LSB of B, rest of bytes could be non zero.
:CALL(divARITH); in: [arithA, arithB] out: [arithRes1: arithA/arithB, arithRes2: arithA%arithB]
0 - A           :JMPN(opCALLDATACOPY) ; //TODO: delegateCall ? use of storageAddr? same in process_tx ?
D               :MSTORE(codecopyHashId) ; set hashId to get bytes from
B               :MEM_ALIGN_WR8 ; only use LSB of B, rest of bytes could be non zero
B - 1 => B  ; decrease 1 byte from length
A + 1 => A  ; increment offset to write the next byte
$ => B          :HASHP(E)   ; read value to write in memory
D               :MSTORE(codecopyHashId) ; set hashId to get bytes from
${getBytecode(A, HASHPOS, 1)}           :HASHP(E)                   ; add bytes to hash contract bytecode
E + B => E ; E ret data offset (memory pointer) of last context, B offset in return data  that want to retrive
B + C => B ; total offset (retdataOffset + dataLen)
E => B ; memory pointer where start to copy memory
E + C => B ; offset return data + len return data must be 0

D => A ; D contains y of point to add (depends of bits k1,k2)
$ => A, E                       :MLOAD(txSrcOriginAddr) ; Address of the origin to A and E
C - 1                           :JMPN(invalidIntrinsicTxNonce) ; Compare nonce state tree with nonce transaction
$ => SR                         :SSTORE ; Store the nonce plus one
%BASE_TX_GAS => E ; Store init intrinsic gas at E
E + %BASE_TX_DEPLOY_GAS => E ; Add 32000 if transaction is a create
B - PC - 1                      :JMPN(defaultOpCode) ; no bytecode treated as 0x00
$ => D          :MLOAD(arithRes1) ; value to pay the sequencer in D
32 - C          :JMPN(errorMLOADMSTORE) ; TDDO Should be unreachable! check it
